## How to Use

1. Read the overlay spec to understand the contract model.
2. Load the hardware + OS VMs relevant to your target machine.
3. Mentally (or via LLM prompt) execute your agent loop against the combined rules.
4. Identify thresholds that would trigger fallbacks, latency injection, or aborts.
5. Refine your agent logic or reliability engine accordingly.
6. Later validate the hot paths on real hardware.

The specs are designed to be human-readable *and* LLM-ingestible. Paste relevant sections into your agent prompts or meta-reasoning system.

